### Issue Description
I've been struggling with this for a while. I don't know if this is expected behavior or not, so I thought I'd share it.
I was playing with the [imshow](https://github.com/IntelRealSense/librealsense/blob/master/wrappers/opencv/imshow/rs-imshow.cpp) example. I replaced every "depth" in the code by "color" and `rs2::frame` to `rs2::video_frame`. Then I decided to use a configuration and just added `cfg.enable_stream(RS2_STREAM_COLOR)` 
The resulting code is as follows:

>     #include <librealsense2/rs.hpp> // Include RealSense Cross Platform API
>     #include <opencv2/opencv.hpp>   // Include OpenCV API
>     int main(int argc, char * argv[])
>     {
> 
>         rs2::config cfg;
> 
>         //Add desired streams to configuration
>         cfg.enable_stream(RS2_STREAM_COLOR);
> 
>         rs2::pipeline pipe;
> 
>         // Start streaming with default recommended configuration
>         pipe.start(cfg);
> 
>         using namespace cv;
>         const auto window_name = "Display Image";
> 
>         while (true)
>         {
>             rs2::frameset data = pipe.wait_for_frames(); // Wait for next set of frames from the camera
>             rs2::video_frame color = data.get_color_frame();
> 
>             // Query frame size (width and height)
>             const int w = color.get_width();
>             const int h = color.get_height();
> 
>             // Create OpenCV matrix of size (w,h) from the colorized color data
>             Mat image(Size(w, h), CV_8UC3, (void*)color.get_data(), Mat::AUTO_STEP);
>             // Update the window with new data
>             imshow(window_name, image);
> 
>             char c = (char) cv::waitKey(25);
>             if(c==27) break;
>         }
> 
>         return EXIT_SUCCESS;
>     }
> 

This code as is rises a _Segmentation fault (core dumped)_ when reaching the `imshow` line. This does not happen with the original example when adding RS2_STREAM_DEPTH nor if no configuration is used. In order to fix this I had to add a second parameter: `cfg.enable_stream(RS2_STREAM_COLOR,RS2_FORMAT_BGR8);`.

My guess is that when only asking for the Color Stream the remaining default parameters are such that imshow is unable to handle the resulting frame, but I'm not quite sure why. Also, as I said above, I don't really know if this is actually expected behavior or not, but it got me nuts for a while.

Hope this helps somebody!

We have just been trying to use `UnionType` but with very little success.

This is a simplified example of what we have been trying, using the latest version `0.7.0`:

```py
from graphene.core.classtypes.uniontype import UnionType
from graphene import ObjectType, String, Field

class Human(ObjectType):
    some_field = String()
    other_field = String()

class Pet(ObjectType):
    yet_another_field = String()

class Thing(UnionType):
    '''Thing union description'''
    class Meta:
        types = [Human, Pet]

class Query(ObjectType):
    thing = Field(Thing)

    def resolve_thing(self, args, info):
        return Thing(some_field='test') # or Human(some_field='test')
```

There are a few more variations that we have tried as well, but didn't work. So how does a full example of using `UnionType` look like?

