## Issue description
The following code in `stl_bind.h`
```cpp
    cl.def(init([](iterable it) {
        auto v = std::unique_ptr<Vector>(new Vector());
        v->reserve(len(it));
        for (handle h : it)
           v->push_back(h.cast<T>());
        return v.release();
    }));
```
is inconsistent, because an iterable does not necessarily have `__len__` defined. Either that should be checked, or an overload for `sequence` should be provided.

